<item>
            <title>[LU-4746] Lustre not using kernel current_umask() function breaks GRSecurity umask handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4746</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.5.0 (and before) do not use the kernel&apos;s default current_umask() function, instead accessing the current process pointer directly with current-&amp;gt;fs-&amp;gt;umask. On a standard kernel this is equivalent, however on a GRSecurity-enabled kernel there&apos;s additional logic in the kernel&apos;s current_umask() function that&apos;s being skipped.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="23557">LU-4746</key>
